{
  "stem": "22979.5",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Only the Jews were gassed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And later on, when, you know-- after '44, after the uprising, the gassing stopped.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So many of them were killed in the Black-- at the Black Wall in Auschwitz between barracks 10 and 11 or in the woods up to Brzezinka.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it happened after, you know, the Hungarian came.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It happened in September.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Hungarian transports came from May until September.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What year? 1944.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And, like I said, thousands and thousands.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I will go back to the SS guard because I didn't finish what he did in the camp, why, you know, I was so anxious to testify [? again ?] him.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He was-- well, like I mentioned, Gottfried [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Weisser ?] was his name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He returned after the war.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He was an SS in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But he came to Auschwitz-- he was on the front, and he lost an eye and other injuries.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "After, you know, recuperating, he got a job in Auschwitz. and he had one glass eye.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "His specialty in Auschwitz was-- in Birkenau-- in Birkenau, not in Auschwitz-- in men's camp, when he saw a young male prisoner working not far away, he stopped him, had to find an empty can of food-- you know, from food-- because they were there-- had to put the boy in the middle of the lagerstrasse, an empty can on his head, and he was shooting-- only young, very young boys.",
      "word_count": 71
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And when he didn't-- when he didn't shoot somebody in his body, again the can.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then he shoot him in his forehead.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "The man fell and bleeding.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Had to get up and again put up the can.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he did it as long he couldn't move anymore and couldn't lift the can.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
